text: Tatiyah () is a village in northern Aleppo Governorate, northwestern Syria. It is located on the Queiq Plain, northeast of Azaz, north of the city of Aleppo, and south of the border with the Turkish province of Kilis. The village administratively belongs to Nahiya Azaz in Azaz District. Nearby localities include Nayarah to the south and Salamah to the west. In the 2004 census, Tatiyah had a population of 76. ==References==
